47:12.264 --> 47:13.743
Don't be late, and just you.

47:13.787 --> 47:14.962
-Hey, wait.

47:15.006 --> 47:17.095
[Telephone clacks]

47:17.138 --> 47:18.879
-I think I swallowed
some Kleenexs.

47:18.923 --> 47:20.054
-[Indistinct] Are you going
to give them

47:20.098 --> 47:21.795
the 40,000 American?

47:21.839 --> 47:26.234
-Of course I'm not going to give
them 40,000 American.

47:26.278 --> 47:29.498
I'm going to give them a beating
that they'll never forget,

47:29.542 --> 47:32.284
whoever they are.

47:32.327 --> 47:33.807
-Okay.

47:33.851 --> 47:35.287
[Indian music playing on radio]

47:35.330 --> 47:36.897
[Tool clicking]

47:36.941 --> 47:45.427
♪

47:45.471 --> 47:54.915
♪

47:54.959 --> 48:00.747
♪

48:00.790 --> 48:02.227
[Children playing]

48:05.708 --> 48:07.885
-I think I see their milk wagon.

48:11.192 --> 48:13.760
-So we're clear, right?
You get the money.

48:13.803 --> 48:17.068
You bring it back here, and only
then you take the diamonds over.

48:17.111 --> 48:18.504
-Roger that.

48:18.547 --> 48:19.853
-I still don't see
why she has to do it.

48:19.897 --> 48:21.855
I mean, it's kind of dangerous.

48:21.899 --> 48:23.509
-She's the one that has
the best disguise.

48:23.552 --> 48:24.945
-It's true, I do.

48:24.989 --> 48:27.121
--I know, but still it's --
-It's okay.

48:27.165 --> 48:29.732
I know we got
each other's back.

48:29.776 --> 48:31.734
[Seatbelts click]

48:31.778 --> 48:32.997
-Give me the cash.

48:41.353 --> 48:43.529
-Looks good, no?
Almost looks real.

48:45.618 --> 48:47.750
-You're engaged to my daughter.

48:47.794 --> 48:49.622
What else do you want?
A bloody medal?

48:49.665 --> 48:53.104
-No, no, no, no.
Just a kind word would be nice.

48:55.236 --> 48:57.238
Now, listen, as soon as I have
the diamonds,

48:57.282 --> 48:59.458
come and grab
whoever's there.

48:59.501 --> 49:01.242
These [speaks native language]
won't mess with me again.

49:01.286 --> 49:02.852
Got it?
-Mm-hmm.

49:02.896 --> 49:04.724
[Birds chirping]

49:10.251 --> 49:12.123
He's lucky to be having me
as a son-in-law.

49:20.740 --> 49:22.046
-He's there.

49:22.089 --> 49:24.483
-You good?
-Oh, yeah.

49:24.526 --> 49:26.311
Super good.

49:27.225 --> 49:29.401
[Birds chirping]

49:31.664 --> 49:41.021
♪

49:41.065 --> 49:50.900
♪

49:50.944 --> 50:00.214
♪

50:00.258 --> 50:07.569
♪

50:07.613 --> 50:12.966
♪

50:13.010 --> 50:16.317
[Groans]

50:16.361 --> 50:18.972
Hello, young sir.

50:19.016 --> 50:20.452
What a lovely morning.

50:20.495 --> 50:23.150
-We can drop the old man act.

50:23.194 --> 50:24.891
I've seen the security footage.

50:24.934 --> 50:27.372
I know how nimble you are.

50:27.415 --> 50:31.245
-I'm going to stay in character,
if you're not be minding.

50:31.289 --> 50:33.639
I'm very committed.

50:33.682 --> 50:35.728
-Where are my diamonds?

50:35.771 --> 50:37.121
-Your money first.

50:39.340 --> 50:41.342
-Here. Now, my diamonds.

50:41.386 --> 50:44.563
-I need to check the paper,
then I get your diamonds.

50:44.606 --> 50:46.434
-There you check.
Now, my diamonds.

50:46.478 --> 50:48.610
-I need to check it properly!

50:48.654 --> 50:50.134
♪

50:50.177 --> 50:51.570
-Done.

50:51.613 --> 50:52.658
-Cash first.
-Diamonds.

50:52.701 --> 50:54.312
[Indistinct shouting]

50:54.355 --> 50:55.878
-It doesn't look like
it's going that well.

50:55.922 --> 50:57.706
-Show me the cash!
-The diamonds, the diamonds!

50:57.750 --> 50:59.752
-Give me the cash!

50:59.795 --> 51:01.014
-Oh.

51:03.451 --> 51:04.713
-You're a very bad man.

51:04.757 --> 51:06.802
-Who are you? Huh?
-[Grunting]

51:06.846 --> 51:08.195
-Who are you?

51:08.239 --> 51:10.502
♪

51:10.545 --> 51:11.764
[Groans]

51:11.807 --> 51:13.113
-[Speaks in native language]

51:13.157 --> 51:14.506
Maybe we should go help?

51:14.549 --> 51:15.985
I mean, he doesn't
have the diamonds.

51:16.029 --> 51:17.378
He said to wait
until he had the diamonds.

51:17.422 --> 51:18.727
Maybe we should just go anyway.
No, no, no.

51:18.771 --> 51:19.772
He might get upset,
but then he might

51:19.815 --> 51:20.773
get upset if you don't go.

51:20.816 --> 51:21.817
So maybe we should just go

51:21.861 --> 51:28.172
♪

51:28.215 --> 51:32.263
[Indistinct shouting]

51:32.306 --> 51:34.134
-Go get her.

51:34.178 --> 51:35.657
♪

51:35.701 --> 51:37.268
-She needs help.

51:37.311 --> 51:38.921
Give me the diamonds.
We'll just give them back.

51:38.965 --> 51:40.140
-No, they don't get them back
till we get the money.

51:40.184 --> 51:41.315
-Just give me the diamonds.

51:41.359 --> 51:42.708
-These aren't even the diamonds!

51:42.751 --> 51:44.057
-What?

51:44.101 --> 51:45.450
-They're pieces
of costume jewelry.

51:45.493 --> 51:47.800
I -- I switched them out.

51:47.843 --> 51:50.672
-This is nothing
like "Sunny and Salim."

51:50.716 --> 51:52.500
♪

51:52.544 --> 51:54.198
-Wait.
You're not in disguise.

51:54.241 --> 51:55.677
They'll know who you are.

51:55.721 --> 52:04.730
♪

52:04.773 --> 52:06.514
-What about you?
-Don't worry about me.

52:06.558 --> 52:07.907
-Okay.

52:07.950 --> 52:09.256
-Go.

52:09.300 --> 52:18.178
♪

52:18.222 --> 52:19.701
-[Screams]

52:19.745 --> 52:27.883
♪

52:27.927 --> 52:30.669
-We have to help him.

52:30.712 --> 52:32.018
-Fine then.

52:32.061 --> 52:41.070
♪

52:41.114 --> 52:43.029
♪

52:43.072 --> 52:44.378
-Get him in the car.

52:44.422 --> 52:53.387
♪

52:53.431 --> 52:56.303
♪

52:56.347 --> 52:58.175
[Engine revs]

53:00.438 --> 53:03.223
-At IIT would say that
this particular hypothesis

53:03.267 --> 53:06.313
has been poked in the face
and proved to be falsifiable.

53:26.203 --> 53:29.249
-You were here a few days ago
making a big song and dance

53:29.293 --> 53:31.382
on my checkout counter.

53:31.425 --> 53:33.079
What is that about?

53:33.122 --> 53:34.341
[Indistinct conversations]

53:34.385 --> 53:35.821
[Chair clacking]

53:37.692 --> 53:39.781
-Tell him, tell him now.

53:39.825 --> 53:41.957
Tell him!
Will you tell him?

53:42.001 --> 53:43.176
Tell him now.

53:43.220 --> 53:45.265
Tell him, tell him.
Tell him!

53:45.309 --> 53:47.267
Tell him, tell him.

53:47.311 --> 53:48.442
Fine.

53:48.486 --> 53:49.748
[Chair clacking]

53:50.879 --> 53:52.446
-And the girl
from the newspaper,

53:52.490 --> 53:53.926
she was here the same time.

53:53.969 --> 53:56.058
Does she have anything
to do with you?

53:56.102 --> 53:59.453
[Chair scraping]

53:59.497 --> 54:01.586
-Tell him.
Tell him now.

54:01.629 --> 54:03.631
Tell him!
Better tell him.

54:03.675 --> 54:05.416
Tell him.
Tell him.

54:06.678 --> 54:08.245
[Chair scraping]

54:12.074 --> 54:15.077
-Would you like a soda?

54:15.121 --> 54:16.818
How about a soda?

54:16.862 --> 54:18.255
-Yes?

54:18.298 --> 54:26.088
♪

54:26.132 --> 54:27.655
[Soda can pops]

54:27.699 --> 54:29.353
♪

54:29.396 --> 54:31.006
A soda.

54:31.050 --> 54:33.270
-Take it!
Better take it.

54:33.313 --> 54:34.619
Drink it, yeah.

54:39.450 --> 54:41.234
-Did you guys see?

54:41.278 --> 54:42.714
-I think you're trying
to force him to drink

54:42.757 --> 54:44.106
some kind of truth serum.

54:44.150 --> 54:45.978
-We've got to get him
out of there.

54:46.021 --> 54:48.372
Any ideas?

54:48.415 --> 54:51.026
-Oh, yeah, I got one.

54:51.070 --> 54:52.419
-What is it?

54:52.463 --> 54:55.030
-We go in through the roof.
-The roof?

54:55.074 --> 54:57.685
-By way of a helicopter.
[Helicopter blades whirring]

54:57.729 --> 55:00.079
They'll never be expecting it.

55:00.122 --> 55:01.907
We lay down
some plastic explosives

55:01.950 --> 55:03.691
in a really neat circle.

55:03.735 --> 55:08.392
Or better get in the shape
of a rangoli so it's auspicious.

55:08.435 --> 55:10.959
The explosives are wired
to a remote.

55:11.003 --> 55:13.005
We press it, and it blows
a hole in the roof.

55:13.048 --> 55:14.398
[Explosion]

55:14.441 --> 55:16.965
Then we jump through
the hole and rescue him.

55:17.009 --> 55:18.010
No, you're right.

55:18.053 --> 55:20.404
[Speech rewinding]

55:20.447 --> 55:22.362
We don't have any rope.

55:22.406 --> 55:25.887
-Does anyone have a doable idea
of how we can get in there?

55:25.931 --> 55:28.063
-You could always
try walking in.

55:28.107 --> 55:30.196
-Unless you're really dumb.

55:31.980 --> 55:33.330
-So, these are the four idiots

55:33.373 --> 55:35.288
who thought
they could steal from me.

55:35.332 --> 55:37.159
-Now, even your friends realize

55:37.203 --> 55:41.076
what an American-born
loser you are.

55:41.120 --> 55:43.905
-You two acquainted?

55:43.949 --> 55:45.603
-He used to date Rina,

55:45.646 --> 55:48.214
until she realized
what a deadbeat he was

55:48.257 --> 55:53.306
and dumped his ass
and found herself a real man.

55:53.350 --> 55:56.178
-You used to date my daughter?

55:56.222 --> 55:58.833
-For two years.

55:58.877 --> 56:00.444
I was in and out
of your house.

56:00.487 --> 56:03.316
I went out for dinner
with you and everything.

56:03.360 --> 56:05.144
You don't remember me?

56:05.187 --> 56:07.451
-I have no recollection.
-[Chuckles]

56:07.494 --> 56:09.583
But here is one thing I do know.

56:09.627 --> 56:12.281
I want you to take
this other idiot

56:12.325 --> 56:14.371
my daughter is now engaged to...

56:14.414 --> 56:18.113
-That's me.
-...and bring back my diamonds.

56:18.157 --> 56:19.811
-You mean your dirty diamonds.

56:19.854 --> 56:22.161
-What do you mean,
dirty diamonds?

56:22.204 --> 56:23.989
They belong to
my great grandmother.

56:24.032 --> 56:25.991
And the only thing dirty
about those diamonds

56:26.034 --> 56:29.168
where the four British soldier
she killed

56:29.211 --> 56:31.039
when they tried
to steal them from her.

56:31.083 --> 56:33.390
[Bird cawing]

56:33.433 --> 56:34.739
[Indian music playing on radio]

56:34.782 --> 56:38.960
♪

56:39.004 --> 56:40.788
-Hey, I'm just going
to pick something up.

56:40.832 --> 56:42.486
♪

56:42.529 --> 56:45.619
-Hello, auntie.
How are you?

56:45.663 --> 56:47.360
-You friend of Vinny?

56:47.404 --> 56:48.622
-Oh, yes.

56:48.666 --> 56:51.799
In his dreams.

56:51.843 --> 56:55.803
-Mom, have you seen a tin
in here

56:55.847 --> 56:58.458
with costume jewelry?

56:58.502 --> 57:00.417
-You mean this one?

57:00.460 --> 57:04.551
-[Sighs]
[Sewing machine whirring]

57:04.595 --> 57:06.510
What happened to
the stuff inside?

57:06.553 --> 57:09.034
-Oh, the pieces of glass?

57:09.077 --> 57:12.124
I used them to decorate
King Ashoka's crown,

57:12.167 --> 57:15.388
and he sparked.
[Clicks tongue]

57:15.432 --> 57:17.042
-The King Ashoka?

57:28.183 --> 57:30.055
It stuck on Ashoka's crown?

57:30.098 --> 57:31.535
-Uh-huh.

57:31.578 --> 57:34.581
-I can't take King Ashoka's
crown, bro.

57:34.625 --> 57:36.844
It's India's
greatest emperor.

57:36.888 --> 57:39.325
He slaughtered thousands,
felt bad about it,

57:39.368 --> 57:40.892
then became a Buddhist.

57:48.682 --> 57:51.250
-Looks like he's ready
to hand it over anyway.

57:51.293 --> 57:52.556
-[Sighs]

57:54.819 --> 57:56.734
-King Ashoka.

57:56.777 --> 57:58.083
Please forgive me.
-Hey, Hey!

57:58.126 --> 57:59.432
-I can't believe you lied to me!

57:59.476 --> 58:00.694
[Indistinct shouting]

58:00.738 --> 58:05.525
♪

58:05.569 --> 58:06.961
[All slurping]

58:11.749 --> 58:13.185
[Door opens]

58:13.228 --> 58:16.449
[Speaks native language]
I brought you diamonds.

58:25.632 --> 58:27.112
-Go.

58:34.554 --> 58:36.513
-I had to fight
King Ashoka for this.

58:36.556 --> 58:37.775
[Door closes]

58:37.818 --> 58:39.167
I won.

58:40.952 --> 58:42.823
He lost.

58:42.867 --> 58:48.046
♪

58:48.089 --> 58:50.875
-Well, at least we tried.

58:50.918 --> 58:52.703
-Tried is not good enough.

58:52.746 --> 58:55.140
Not when you're back in
the same place you was before.

58:55.183 --> 58:56.837
-Hey, it's not all bad.

58:56.881 --> 58:59.318
My mother lovin' green card
came in the mail today.

58:59.361 --> 59:01.538
-That's great.
Congratulations.

59:01.581 --> 59:03.757
-Yeah, I'm very friggin
happy for you.

59:03.801 --> 59:05.585
But what about Zak here?

59:05.629 --> 59:07.500
He don't get to go to Bollywood
and achieve his dreams.

59:07.544 --> 59:09.894
-I cooled on that idea anyway.

59:09.937 --> 59:13.462
I've got plenty
of dreaming to do here.

59:13.506 --> 59:15.377
-You sweetheart.

59:15.421 --> 59:17.771
Oh, and an angel investor
told me he wants to take

59:17.815 --> 59:19.730
Great Little India Times
online

59:19.773 --> 59:21.253
as a self uploading
video portal

59:21.296 --> 59:22.733
automatic blockchain, NFT,
social media

59:22.776 --> 59:24.778
sharing site for charity.

59:24.822 --> 59:26.519
-Yeah, that is great.

59:26.563 --> 59:28.956
But my Kalyani auntie's
heart valves are still shot,

59:29.000 --> 59:30.915
and she don't got no money
for an operation.

59:30.958 --> 59:34.658
-It was
[speaks native language] auntie.

59:34.701 --> 59:36.790
I got that wrong, by the way.

59:36.834 --> 59:38.009
-Got what wrong!

59:38.052 --> 59:39.706
-It wasn't heart valve.

59:39.750 --> 59:42.448
She was talking about
the plumbing in her bathroom.

59:42.491 --> 59:44.276
She needed some kind
of new valves there.

59:44.319 --> 59:46.060
But still pretty expensive.

59:46.104 --> 59:50.978
Gave her heart palpitations
when she saw the bill.

59:51.022 --> 59:53.981
-Well, she should be dying.

59:54.025 --> 59:57.202
You all should be dying,
like I am.

59:57.245 --> 59:58.420
Dying.

1:00:00.074 --> 1:00:02.120
Because Rina's still engaged.

1:00:02.163 --> 1:00:03.600
Nothing's changed.

1:00:03.643 --> 1:00:05.079
[Wind blowing]

1:00:11.999 --> 1:00:20.617
♪

1:00:20.660 --> 1:00:24.359
♪

1:00:24.403 --> 1:00:27.667
[Bell chimes]

1:00:27.711 --> 1:00:31.628
-So, tell me.

1:00:31.671 --> 1:00:33.673
What's going on?

1:00:33.717 --> 1:00:35.457
-I don't know.

1:00:35.501 --> 1:00:37.242
But ever since Rina
broke up with me,

1:00:37.285 --> 1:00:39.418
I've been too scared
to do anything.

1:00:39.461 --> 1:00:40.941
And then when I finally
did do something,

1:00:40.985 --> 1:00:42.334
I didn't do what I thought
it was going to do.

1:00:42.377 --> 1:00:44.728
So, why do anything at all?

1:00:48.470 --> 1:00:51.256
-Sometimes the doing
doesn't always reap

1:00:51.299 --> 1:00:53.171
the rewards we expect.

1:00:53.214 --> 1:00:56.261
Sometimes we gain
and we lose other things.

1:00:56.304 --> 1:00:58.611
And sometimes
we have to ask ourselves

1:00:58.655 --> 1:01:01.309
are we doing the right doing.

1:01:01.353 --> 1:01:04.922
Or are we just do-doing it out?

1:01:04.965 --> 1:01:09.143
-Was being my dad just
do-doing around for you?

1:01:09.187 --> 1:01:11.537
-Is that why you cut out
on me and Mom?

1:01:13.408 --> 1:01:15.584
-I didn't cut out on you.

1:01:15.628 --> 1:01:19.501
I'm still here.
I'm still around.

1:01:19.545 --> 1:01:23.941
It's just my focus
is on higher things.

1:01:23.984 --> 1:01:26.291
-Maybe I needed
some of that focus.

1:01:26.334 --> 1:01:30.730
Maybe I needed you to see me
so I wouldn't be such a loser.

1:01:30.774 --> 1:01:33.080
-I see you.

1:01:33.124 --> 1:01:35.822
-I see the eternal flame in you.

1:01:35.866 --> 1:01:38.695
[Chuckles]

1:01:38.738 --> 1:01:44.265
And in all creatures,
and the plants.

1:01:44.309 --> 1:01:46.441
-But I ain't
a goddamn plant, Dad.

1:01:46.485 --> 1:01:47.704
[Bell chimes]

1:01:47.747 --> 1:01:55.755
♪

1:01:55.799 --> 1:02:05.765
♪

1:02:05.809 --> 1:02:10.378
♪

1:02:10.422 --> 1:02:12.816
-The Chicken Tikka pizza's
tight, huh?

1:02:12.859 --> 1:02:14.339
-Yeah.

1:02:14.382 --> 1:02:16.994
Your dad knows
what he's doing.

1:02:17.037 --> 1:02:19.170
-That's why I gotta
sing about it.

1:02:19.213 --> 1:02:21.912
He's an inspiration.
Like you, Vin.

1:02:21.955 --> 1:02:25.263
-Me? I ain't no inspiration,

1:02:25.306 --> 1:02:27.569
I'm just loser,
like everybody thinks.

1:02:27.613 --> 1:02:31.182
-Yo, cos, you inspire me.
You always have.

1:02:31.225 --> 1:02:32.574
You're the one told me
to find that

1:02:32.618 --> 1:02:34.968
little voice inside me
that's just mine

1:02:35.012 --> 1:02:36.709
and make it big.

1:02:36.753 --> 1:02:39.233
Because that's
your heart's voice, you said.

1:02:39.277 --> 1:02:42.149
-I said that to, huh?
-Yeah, bro. Yous an artist.

1:02:42.193 --> 1:02:44.021
It ain't easy to be an artist.

1:02:44.064 --> 1:02:47.285
Take some dirt digging, and you
got dirt digging in spades.

1:02:47.328 --> 1:02:48.765
-You think?

1:02:48.808 --> 1:02:50.462
-You just gotta believe
you're worthy, bro?

1:02:50.505 --> 1:02:54.074
-It ain't easy when no one else
believes in you.

1:02:54.118 --> 1:02:55.597
-I believe in you.

1:02:57.861 --> 1:02:59.123
-What about you?

1:02:59.166 --> 1:03:00.167
Don't you got your audition

1:03:00.211 --> 1:03:02.213
for the culture show tonight?

1:03:02.256 --> 1:03:04.737
I don't know if I'm going
to put up, though.

1:03:04.781 --> 1:03:07.261
-What do you mean
you ain't going to put up?

1:03:07.305 --> 1:03:09.829
-I don't know if I want to be
a solo artist anymore.

1:03:09.873 --> 1:03:12.484
-Hmm.
[Exhales sharply]

1:03:12.527 --> 1:03:13.790
You need some backup, huh?

1:03:13.833 --> 1:03:16.488
-I need to find me a crew, bro.

1:03:16.531 --> 1:03:20.840
-Yeah, It's better
when you got a crew.

1:03:20.884 --> 1:03:23.800
You know what?
I got you.

1:03:25.279 --> 1:03:26.672
-Cool.

1:03:26.715 --> 1:03:35.942
♪

1:03:35.986 --> 1:03:38.902
♪

1:03:52.611 --> 1:03:55.396
-Thanks for coming.

1:03:55.440 --> 1:03:57.355
I'm sorry I lost it.

1:03:59.618 --> 1:04:04.057
And I really am glad
for you all.

1:04:04.101 --> 1:04:06.277
